C4Container
    title Container Diagram - AresNexus Settlement Core

    System_Boundary(b_settlement_core, "Settlement Core System") {
        Container(api, "API Container", "ASP.NET Core 10.0", "Exposes commands and queries via REST/GraphQL.")
        Container(domain, "Domain Layer", "C# DLL", "Holds the business logic (Aggregates, Policies, Money).")
        Container(infra, "Infrastructure Layer", "C# DLL", "Handles persistence and integration (Marten, Outbox, Messaging).")
        ContainerDb(marten, "Marten (PostgreSQL)", "Relational DB", "Serves as both Event Store and Projection Database.")
        Container(outbox_proc, "Outbox Processor", "Background Service", "Polls and dispatches events asynchronously to external systems.")
        ContainerDb(redis, "Redis", "Key-Value Store", "Provides distributed caching and rate limiting states.")
    }

    Rel(api, domain, "Invokes Commands", "C# Method Calls")
    Rel(domain, infra, "Depends on Repositories", "Interfaces")
    Rel(infra, marten, "Persists Events / Reads Projections", "Npgsql / Marten DSL")
    Rel(infra, redis, "Check/Update Cache/RateLimits", "RESP")
    Rel(outbox_proc, marten, "Reads Outbox Messages / Updates Status", "Advisory Lock + Skip Locked")
    Rel(outbox_proc, infra, "Uses Messaging Client", "C# Interface")

    Note right of marten: Transaction Boundary: Commands are atomic (Event Append + Outbox Insert).
    Note left of outbox_proc: Safe scaling via Postgres Advisory Locks.
    Note bottom of api: Stateless design for horizontal scalability.
